134→    {"option": "PostgreSQL via Docker", "rejected_because": "Violates local-first constraint — requires running a server process"}
135→  ],
136→  "trade_offs": "Requires native compilation (node-gyp) which can fail on some systems. No browser compatibility.",
137→  "revisit_when": "If multi-device sync is added or users report node-gyp build failures.",
138→  "confidence": 92,
139→  "evidence": ["User#3: 'We need something that works without a server'", "Assistant#4: 'better-sqlite3 with WAL mode gives concurrent reads...'"]
140→}
141→
142→EXCELLENT learning:
143→{
144→  "title": "Tailwind v4 requires @theme inline{} for CSS variable utilities",
145→  "symptom": "After Tailwind v3→v4 upgrade, custom utilities like bg-primary stopped working. Classes present in HTML but no styles applied.",
146→  "root_cause": "Tailwind v4 removed tailwind.config.js theme extension. CSS variables in :root are not automatically available as utilities — must be registered via @theme inline {} in the CSS file.",
147→  "takeaway": "When migrating Tailwind v3→v4 with shadcn/ui: add @theme inline {} mapping CSS variables, add @custom-variant dark for class-based dark mode, replace tailwindcss-animate with tw-animate-css.",
